Philippine Stocks: PLDT Communications, Robinsons Land, SM

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-02T04:21:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/philippine-stocks-pldt-communications-robinsons-land-sm.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index decreased 0.3 percent
to 3,773.71.  Developers: Robinsons Land Corp. (RLC PM), the nation’s
fourth-largest homebuilder by market value, slid 2.3 percent to
12 pesos, the most since Feb. 23.  Megaworld Corp . (MEG PM), the
second-biggest, slid 2.8 percent to 2.08 pesos, the steepest
retreat since Feb. 22. Central bank Governor Amando Tetangco
said yesterday rising oil and foods costs leave the monetary
authority less scope to keep borrowing costs at a record low.    PLDT Communications and Energy Ventures Inc . (PCEV PM),
which owns shares in Manila Electric Co., sank 12 percent to
6.50 pesos, the steepest loss since Oct. 27, 2008. Chairman
Manuel Pangilinan said yesterday he prefers the company to be
delisted from the stock exchange.    SM Development Corp . (SMDC PM), the nation’s third-largest
builder, rose 3.3 percent to 7.29 pesos, the steepest gain since
Dec. 30. The builder will distribute 1.1 billion shares as a
stock dividend and its board approved raising its capital to
12.4 billion pesos, a stock exchange filing showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
